    <item>
      <title>Nagios notify via MS-Teams</title>
      <link>https://www.mikecone.us/post/devops/nagios_notify_msteams/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 22 Mar 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.mikecone.us/post/devops/nagios_notify_msteams/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I published a new project to GitHub today: 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/mrmikee/nagios-notify-msteams&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Nagios MS-Teams notifications&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This project sends alerts about hosts and services via MS-Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;img/example-service-notice.png&#34; alt=&#34;screenshot of nagios alert&#34; width=&#34;400&#34;/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m using Python with Jinja2 templates to send Simple messages and 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/adaptive-cards/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Microsoft&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;Adaptive Cards&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; to MS-Teams via an &amp;ldquo;Incoming Webhook&amp;rdquo;.  This is not a bot, just a simple way for me to send nagios alerts.  For outages the fewer the moving parts of your alerting system the better.  Never depend on just one method of alerting.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
